.TH "ep_loop_check" 9 "ep_loop_check" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ep_loop_check \- Performs a check to verify that adding an epoll file (@to) into another epoll file (represented by @from) does not create closed loops or too deep chains.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ep_loop_check
.BI "(struct eventpoll *ep "  ","
.BI "struct eventpoll *to "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ep" 12
-- undescribed --
.IP "to" 12
Pointer to the epoll to be inserted.
.SH "RETURN"
Returns zero if adding the epoll \fIto\fP inside the epoll \fIfrom\fP
does not violate the constraints, or -1 otherwise.
